text: Sheikh Buddin National Park (also spelled Sheikh Badin National Park) is in Dera Ismail Khan District, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. The park was established in 2003 and covers an area of 15,540 hectares. == Related pages == * Dera Ismail Khan District Category:National parks in Pakistan Category:Dera Ismail Khan District
title: Sheikh Buddin National Park
